Titanic Survival Prediction - End-to-End PyTorch Pipeline


This project implements a complete machine learning pipeline to predict Titanic passenger survival using a Deep Learning approach with PyTorch. 

The solution includes data fetching from Kaggle, Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), a standalone training script, and an interactive Streamlit dashboard for inference and visualization.



Project Structure


├── .env                  # Your private Kaggle credentials (not tracked by Git)
├── .env.example          # Template for environment variables
├── .gitignore            # Files to ignore (including .env and model artifacts)
├── ds_app.py             # Streamlit Inference UI
├── train.py              # Standalone training script
├── model_utils.py        # Utility functions: Data cleaning, NN architecture
├── Data_Science_Home_Assignment_Segev_Ohana.ipynb     # Jupyter Notebook for Exploratory Data Analysis
├── requirements.txt      # Project dependencies
├── run_app_script.bat    # Batch file to run the full pipeline
└── README.md             # Project documentation


